95.6	Plame_affair	Plame affair	The Plame Affair (also known as the CIA leak scandal, the CIA leak case, the CIA leak grand jury investigation, and Plamegate) involved the identification of Valerie Plame Wilson as a covert Central Intelligence Agency officer. Mrs. Wilson's relationship with the CIA was formerly classified information. The disclosure was made in a Washington Post column entitled "Mission to Niger" written by Robert Novak, and published on July 14, 2003.	
